# Case Study: Wazuh SIEM Lab for Endpoint Monitoring and SOC Triage

## Executive Summary

This project demonstrates a Wazuh-based SIEM lab designed to practice endpoint monitoring, alert review, file integrity monitoring, vulnerability visibility, and basic SOC investigation workflow.

The goal of this project was not only to install Wazuh, but to understand how a SOC analyst can use a SIEM to collect endpoint telemetry, review alerts, investigate suspicious activity, document findings, and recommend remediation steps.

## Project Objective

The main objectives of this lab were to:

* Deploy a working Wazuh SIEM environment.
* Connect monitored endpoints using Wazuh agents.
* Validate endpoint visibility from the Wazuh dashboard.
* Review security alerts generated from endpoint activity.
* Practice basic SOC triage and incident documentation.
* Understand how SIEM data supports detection, response, and remediation.

